name: wax production, for lost-wax metal casting | wax, lost-wax casting | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/11546/documentation

This dataset represents the production of wax for lost-wax casting (or investment casting).; Wax used in this type of casting is a mixture of different types of wax (both petroleum wax and natural), resins (both from synthetic and natural origin) and organic fillers. The composition of the wax vary from facility to facility. The wax pattern produced defines de quality of the final casting. This dataset is a copy of the ecoinvent v3.0 dataset "paraffin production, GLO 1995" used as proxy. Uncertainties have been adjusted accordinly.



"This module contains material and energy input, production of waste and emissions for the production of n-paraffins out of crude oil. Water consumption and infrastructure have been estimated." as cited in original dataset.
category: C:Manufacturing/19:Manufacture of coke and refined petroleum products/192:Manufacture of refined petroleum products/1920:Manufacture of refined petroleum products

processDocumentation.timeDescription: "data of published literature" as cited in original dataset.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: "Data based on the European paraffin production" as cited in original dataset.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: "Average technology, typical for European production conditions in the mid 90s" as cited in original dataset.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: "data out of ECOSOL study of European Surfactant Industry. Common translation rules used, reported in Chemical report (Althaus et al. 2003). This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography RER. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly." as cited in the original dataset.
